Program: Outlook
Title: Kiev Protester: "I Was Tortured"
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01rqkpg
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 13 Feb 2014
Ukrainian anti-government protester Dmytro Bulatov tells us from hospital that he was kidnapped and tortured before being dumped outside Kiev. Finding a thousand ways to say "I love you": Alassane Maiga is the Malian scribe working night and day to compose Valentine's cards for customers. How does Bollywood portray women? Tom Brook reports from Mumbai following national soul-searching over attacks on women. And meet Finland's first black MP: hear Jani Toivola on discovering his roots in Kenya. Picture: Dmytro Bulatov displays wounds on his hands and face Picture credit: Petras Malukas/AFP/Getty Images Show less